Q1) Check if number is a perfect number or not

Problem Output Statement:

Test case 1:
     Enter a number: 6
     6 is a perfect number since Σi=0,13=13 for all 13%i=0

Test Case 2:
     Enter a number: 13
     13 is not a perfect number since Σi=0,13!=13 for all 13%i==0



Solution-->


OR
https://www.hackerrank.com/challenges/grading/editorial

Code-->
void solution() {
     int n, x;
     cin>>n;
     for(int i=0; i<n; i++){
        cin>>x;
        if(x>=38 and x%5>=3){
            while(x%5!=0){
               x++;
            }
        }
        cout<<x<<endl;
     }
}

int main () {
    solution();
    return 0;
}

Problem Output Statement:

Test case 1:
     Enter the average marks: 74
     The final grade is 75
     
Test case 2:
     Enter the average marks: 71
     The final grade is 71

Test case 3:
     Enter the average marks: 36
