#controversial Q3) Given an array of integers, and a divisor variable x print all elements that are divisible by x. Solve the problem without using the '/' or '%' or any other division operator

Q4) aaaaa
    a   a
    a   a
    aaaaa

OR

Given n= number of lines to print and x=an integer print table of x in the following way:

e.g x=5, n=4

5
10 15
20 25 30 
35 40 45 50

Code-->
#include<stdio.h>
#include<conio.h>
void main()
{
int num=1,n,x,i,j;
clrscr();
printf("Enter number of lines:");
scanf("%d",&n);
printf("Enter number X:");
scanf("%d",&x);
for(i=0;i<n;i++)
{
for(j=0;j<=i;j++)
{
printf("%d ",num*x);
num+=1;
}
printf("\n");
}
getch();
}

Q5) Toggle Case of characters in a string.  

Code-->

#include <stdio.h>
#include <string.h>
void main()
{
  char str1[100];
  printf("Enter a string:");
  gets(str1);
  for(int i=0;str1[i]!='\0';i++)
  {
    if(str1[i]>='a' && str1[i]<='z')
       str1[i] = str1[i] - 32;
    else if(str1[i]>='A' && str1[i]<='Z')
       str1[i] = str1[i] + 32;
  }
  printf("given string in toggled state:%s",str1);
}


Problem Output Statement:

Test case 1:
     Enter a string: AbaSBSANXbsha
     aBAsbsanxBSHA
     
Test case 2:
     Enter a string: ashcDD
     ASHCdd

